President Barack Obama has announced his intention to nominate Rabbi David Nathan Saperstein as Ambassador at Large for International Religious Freedom in the Department of State. Rabbi Saperstein currently serves as the Director and Counsel of the Religious Action Center of Reform Judaism and as an Adjunct Professor of Law at Georgetown University Law Center. He has also served on various boards and commissions, including the U.S. Commission on International Religious Freedom and the President's Advisory Council on Faith-Based and Neighborhood Partnerships. Rabbi Saperstein holds a B.A. from Cornell University, an M.H.L. from Hebrew Union College, and a J.D. from American University. President Obama expressed his gratitude for Rabbi Saperstein's dedication to serving the American people and looks forward to working with him in the future.